        "title": "Best practice for method with Map return",
        "body": "<p>Suppose i have a method which has map as return type and uses generics.<\/p>\n\n<p>I would like to know what is the best practice of filling that Map object.\nPlease see the snippet.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public Map&lt;String,?&gt; getEmployeeInfo(String query) {\n\nMap&lt;String,Object&gt; dataMap = new HashMap&lt;String,Object&gt;();\n\n    // do some op.\n\n    String empId = \"abc123\";\n\n    List&lt;Long&gt; projectIds = new ArrayList&lt;Long&gt;();\n\n    List&lt;String&gt; performanceGoals = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();\n\n\n    dataMap.put(\"empId\",empId);\n    dataMap.put(\"projectIds\",projectIds);\n    dataMap.put(\"performanceGoals\",performanceGoals);\n\n    return dataMap;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
